     "linear algebra", "vector space", "Hermitian product", 
      "Frobenius inner product", "inner product"}, "specialkeywords" -> {}, 
    "tutorialcollectionlinks" -> {}, "index" -> True, "label" -> 
    "Quantum Mob/ Q3 Symbol", "language" -> "en", "paclet" -> "QuantumMob/Q3",
     "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "HilbertSchmidtProduct[a, b] returns the Hilbert-Schmidt inner product \
(also known as Frobenius inner product) of two complex matrices a and b. \
HilbertSchmidtProduct[a, b, {s1, s2, ...}] returns the Hilbert-Schmidt inner \
product of linear operators a and b on species {s1, s2, ...}. If {s1, s2, \
...} is unspecified and missing, the list of species is found from the \
expressions for a and b. HilbertSchmidtProduct[{s1, s2, ...}] represents an \
operator form of HilbertSchmidtProduct that can be applied to a pair of \
linear operators.", "synonyms" -> {}, "tabletags" -> {}, "title" -> 
